 Forecast Discussion






   SPC AC 280728

   Day 3 Convective Outlook  
   NWS Storm Prediction Center Norman OK
   0228 AM CDT Fri Jul 28 2017

   Valid 301200Z - 311200Z

   ...NO SEVERE THUNDERSTORM AREAS FORECAST...

   ...SUMMARY...
   Severe thunderstorms are unlikely on Sunday across the contiguous
   USA.

   ...Synopsis and discussion...
   A weak upper low will remain over the Mid Atlantic with modest
   northerly flow aloft stretching from the Great Lakes to Florida.
   Weak flow aloft will exist across the central and western states,
   with primary jet stream across Canada. At the surface, high pressure
   will stretch from the central Rockies across the Plains and into the
   Midwest, providing relatively stable conditions. A surface trough
   will exist across the western Atlantic, extending southwestward
   across northern Florida and into the central Gulf of Mexico.

   The greatest threat of thunderstorms will occur during the afternoon
   across the Rockies, and more specifically from Colorado into New
   Mexico where easterly flow around the high will maintain 50s F
   dewpoints. However, shear will be quite weak and unsupportive of
   severe weather.

   Elsewhere, daytime storms are likely across Florida in the vicinity
   of the wind shift, and near sea breeze boundaries where a tropical
   air mass will exist.

   ..Jewell.. 07/28/2017

